<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1763,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,345,1763,1789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species is named in honor Prof. Dr. Nusret Ayyıldız in appreciation of his studies of Turkish mites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1763,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,339,1838,1864]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Discussion:</emphasis>
Due to the rugose integument, Cx-I medially separated, Cx-III with a medial glandularium, gnathosomal rostrum, shorter than gnathosomal base, more elongate and pointed, P- 
<number box="[1132,1146,1876,1902]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
with a short ventrodistal projection and excretory pore not surrounded by a sclerotized ring, the new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1907" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1907" box="[151,594,1950,1976]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thienemanni">
<emphasis box="[151,413,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Sperchon thienemanni</emphasis>
Koenike, 
<number box="[533,594,1950,1976]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" value="1907.0">1907</number>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs in the presence of one thick lateral seta on ventral margin of P- 
<number box="[302,316,1988,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,252]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,342,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Variability:</emphasis>
In females, we found variability (often in the same specimen) in P- 
<number box="[1177,1190,152,178]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" value="3.0">3</number>
bearing two ventral setae, situated side by side, the medial one slightly further from the ventral edge of the segment. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,226,252]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[629,679,226,252]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
locality in Bingöl Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1103,226,252]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
